node.text: In episode 1 of Bio-hack your best life, @elisabethihoekstra and @billycarsonofficial go deep into Elisabeth’s story. Who, what, where, when, why? Overcoming a life full of trauma, drama, and addiction, Elisabeth has worn many hats. From modeling/acting, chef life, real estate, the political arena, the mental health world, to now her position with the multi million dollar company 4biddenknowledge as the Director of Operations, Elisabeth has seen and been through it all defeating her shadows along the way. #4biddenknowledge #billycarsonofficial #BillyCarson #biohackyourbestlife

The fires crept up the hills, scattered and grew, helped by the wind, and raced down towards the shore. In some places, desperate locals rushed to the sea, filling up plastic buckets with water to ward off the flames approaching their homes. Others ran or drove for their lives. The sky turned grey, then orange. By the time the smoke had cleared, stretches of Turkey’s coastal paradise, once covered in pine forests and olive trees, were in ashes.

At least eight people have died in the fires along Turkey’s southern and western coasts at the end of July, following record temperatures and a severe drought. Thousands more have been evacuated, including tourists from seaside resorts, some boarding boats to escape. Nearly 160,000 hectares of forest have burned in Turkey this year, according to the European Forest Fire Information System
